{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"22e68df6-9015-44b8-9afd-22d4ce066f2a","content":"No, you **don't need `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` anymore**. In .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively integrates with Microsoft.Testing.Platform. That property was a .NET 9 opt-in bridge and is now obsolete.\n\nYour project already has `EnableMSTestRunner=true`, which makes it an MTP-based project. Just remove the unnecessary property:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01N8UJFm7mHt5A3tYdsgtHG7","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing obsolete property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_013n8s6QAywGcjd8m975FA2K","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-8a1f7f435e7048069b866ef4f5a502ce/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-8a1f7f435e7048069b866ef4f5a502ce/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"d324a9d9-9d9e-4275-81c4-c781ae8edcba","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK and wants to know about Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) support. Let me provide accurate information.\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) without needing the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property. This was a key change in .NET 10 — the new `dotnet test` integration with MTP is built-in.\n\nKey points:\n1. In .NET 10, `dotnet test` uses MTP natively when the test project is an MTP-based project (which it is, since `EnableMSTestRunner` is set to `true`, making it an executable with the MTP runner).\n\n\n2. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property was required in .NET 9 to enable MTP support through `dotnet test`, but it's now redundant in .NET 10 since the platform has native support built in.\n3. With .NET 10, projects using `EnableMSTestRunner=true` or equivalent framework settings are automatically recognized as MTP projects, so they can safely remove that property.","outputTokens":692,"requestId":"703C:D37CE:DEDFEDC:F51CDEE:69F2A8E4"},"id":"71e41813-cb40-4aba-9b98-25e7e935f0cb","timestamp":"2026-04-30T00:57:21.721Z","parentId":"37154aae-551c-4f63-ab80-4defe18dccc5"}
